title="Bijection"
addr="jms-00KR"
type="local">bijections</fr:link> between finite sets</fr:title><fr:taxon>Proposition</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>For all finite sets <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex>, we have:</fr:p><fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[
 \mathord {\#}{\mathrm {Bij}{\mathopen {}\left (A,B\right )\mathclose {}}} =
 \begin {cases}
  0 &\text {if } \mathord {\#}{A}\not =\mathord {\#}{B}\\
  n!&\text {if } \mathord {\#}{A}=\mathord {\#}{B}=n
 \end {cases}
]]></fr:tex>
 
   
